From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000010 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petr.parkan.janda@oh-so.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:10:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] drm/omapdrm: hdmi4: cap pixel clock to known-good (steelhead)

On the Nexus Q the OMAP4 HDMI PLL does not cleanly generate the pixel clocks of
the higher modes the monitor advertises (1440x900@106.5MHz, 1280x1024@108MHz):
the TMDS link comes up but the sink cannot lock, so the panel detects a signal
yet stays blank. The hdmi4 bridge had no .mode_valid, so every EDID mode was
offered to userspace and the compositor (wlroots) selected the EDID-preferred
1440x900 -> blank desktop (boot fbcon at the cmdline mode was visible, which
masked it). Neither the monitor (140MHz max) nor the HDMI PHY (186MHz) is the
limit; it is an omapdrm mode-set/PLL issue specific to these modes.

Add a .mode_valid that caps the advertised pixel clock at 75MHz, so a
displayable mode is selected (keeps 1280x720@74.25 and 1024x768@65, rejects the
blank-inducing 1440x900/1280x1024). Pair with video=HDMI-A-1:1280x720@60.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petr.parkan.janda@oh-so.com>
---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/omapdrm/dss/hdmi4.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/omapdrm/dss/hdmi4.c
@@ -491,8 +491,28 @@
 	return drm_edid;
 }
 
+/*
+ * Steelhead: the OMAP4 HDMI PLL does not cleanly generate the pixel clocks of
+ * the higher modes the monitor advertises (e.g. 1440x900@106.5MHz,
+ * 1280x1024@108MHz): TMDS comes up but the sink cannot lock and the screen
+ * stays blank. The HDMI bridge had no .mode_valid, so these modes were offered
+ * to userspace and the compositor picked the EDID-preferred 1440x900 -> blank
+ * desktop. Cap the advertised pixel clock to a known-good value so a
+ * displayable mode is selected. (~75MHz keeps 1280x720@74 and 1024x768@65.)
+ */
+static enum drm_mode_status
+hdmi4_bridge_mode_valid(struct drm_bridge *bridge,
+			const struct drm_display_info *info,
+			const struct drm_display_mode *mode)
+{
+	if (mode->clock > 75000)
+		return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
+	return MODE_OK;
+}
+
 static const struct drm_bridge_funcs hdmi4_bridge_funcs = {
 	.attach = hdmi4_bridge_attach,
+	.mode_valid = hdmi4_bridge_mode_valid,
 	.mode_set = hdmi4_bridge_mode_set,
 	.atomic_duplicate_state = drm_atomic_helper_bridge_duplicate_state,
 	.atomic_destroy_state = drm_atomic_helper_bridge_destroy_state,
